        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Moomaw, or near Hot Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Warm Springs...
Hot Springs...
Lake Moomaw...
Mountain Grove...
Burnsville...
Bacova Junction...
and Callison.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
